<item>
            <title>[LU-13934] ldev.conf should consider multiple failover nodes</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13934</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;ldev.conf appears to specify a primary and single failover node (&lt;a href=&quot;http://doc.lustre.org/lustre_manual.xhtml#dbdoclet.zfssnapshotConfig&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://doc.lustre.org/lustre_manual.xhtml#dbdoclet.zfssnapshotConfig&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, It&apos;s not necessarily the case that resources are limited to a primary and failover pair; there may be more placements than two.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For example, Exascaler HA is configured such that an OST could be mounted on any of&#160; four available VMs.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It seems that we should expand the ldev.conf such that multiple failovers could be listed after the primary.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
